<br>
Can anyone please shed some light on this and provide me with an answer so I don't waste my time, cuz I really want that proc item at the end of all this!<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/4/01 2:35:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nope, it's not broken</span><hr size=1> It was, but it isn't now. You should be able to finish all three in one night. <p>--Gwynhyfar Foxfyre<br>
<a href="http://thedruidsgrove.org">The Druids Grove</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=felessan>Felessan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/5/01 3:41:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nope, it's not broken</span><hr size=1> *nod* Did these over a few days in the last week - currently working on the Disciple again so I've got the PR / DR buff available.<br>
<br>
Just a note for those thinking of doing it - I'd camp the necro (Larik?) *first*, killing random wandering undead during the 15 minutes between his PH spawns - I managed to get 4 more hearts while doing this bit easily. <p>Felessan<BR>
Wood-elf wanderer of the Fourth Wall<br>
Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umisomiatuc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miso Miatuc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/5/01 5:08:00 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nope, it's not broken</span><hr size=1> Where does this quest begin?  I have heard of this quest two times now and I am darn right curious now.  I wish I had a lot more time to read more about this game.  I am missing way to much.<br>
<br>
 <p>Miso Miatuc<BR>51th Season Druid<BR>
ECI Server<BR>
AVATARA<BR>
www.eqavatara.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaenarawyldhart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aenara Wyldhart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/5/01 12:13:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My Findings</span><hr size=1> I finally finished the quest last Saturday. I've been hung up on the Necro for about two months myself. <br>
<br>
What I would do is park my pet right on the two undead spawns right next to the shrine. They would <B>usually</B> aggro them and Jabeker would kick their rotting asses. This let me torment Brownies and chat while watching spawns. Once I dropped Larik Z`Vole, I went East immediately. The courrier is in run mode and you don't want him to reach the DE camp (the Priestess is a Bitch!).<br>
<br>
After 44, you can easily solo Goblins in SolA for their powder (keep Chloro and DS up). I got a friend who was playing in SK to get me some white hellebore. I offered to help a group in MM to get to the butler in exchange for letting me drop an offerer -- two were up when I zoned in (even at 56 I'm hesistant to solo inside the castle -- those casters are so naughty!).<br>
<br>
I happily retired my Chrysoberl Talisman for the final symbol. Hang in there and get it! The Archive Section has a complete <A HREF="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm18.showMessage?topicID=18.topic">spoiler</A> for your convenience. <p><TABLE WIDTH=575 CELLPADDING=5><TR><TD BGCOLOR="#AAAACC"><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=53547"><IMG ALIGN="RIGHT" BORDER=0 SRC="http://www.xmission.com/~rare/off/help.gif" ALT="Details"></A><A HREF="mailto:aenara@excite.com"><IMG ALIGN="RIGHT" BORDER=0 SRC="http://www.xmission.com/~rare/off/note.gif" ALT="eMail me!"></A><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=+1 COLOR="WHITE">Aenara Wyldhart</B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=2 COLOR="YELLOW">Preserver, Soldier of Tunare, <B>56</B>th Season, <A HREF="http://pub5.ezboard.com/badventurersanonymous">Adventurers Anonymous</A>, Prexus Server</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=1 COLOR="BLUE" FACE="Times New Roman">Master Tailor, Jeweler, Blacksmith, Baker, Brewer, Forager, Tracker, Lush, Potter, Angler, 1hb, Evoker. Solo'n Queen.</FONT><BR>
<FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="WHITE">Aelora Panacea <FONT SIZE=1 COLOR="YELLOW" FACE="Times New Roman">(Vicar of Tunare, 52nd Circle)</FONT></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jedius98>Jedius98</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/7/01 1:44:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> One More Question</span><hr size=1> I jsut finished the second part, who do I turn the stone candle into? Yeorn says lady Trinali or something in Erudin, there is a woman in the enchanter guild w/ that first name who asks about her husband...is that her?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/7/01 4:28:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yes</span><hr size=1> That's her. Forget that stuff about her husband.  <p>--Gwynhyfar Foxfyre<br>
<a href="http://thedruidsgrove.org">The Druids Grove</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jedius98>Jedius98</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/7/01 7:46:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Brewing Now!</span><hr size=1> So am I correct now that I have the items I have to brew them? I will wait for help on this, and if so what lvl should my brewing be when i try?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugalasen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GalaSen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/8/01 10:06:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Initiate of Tunare</span><hr size=1> There is a brew barrel near the zone to Tox Forest .. inside Blue Hawks.  Place the item received from Trilani, the pouch of red sand, the white hellebore and the caustic fluid inside and combine .. item is no drop so be sure not to place back in brew barrel and shut door.. item will poof.  No skill in brewing is needed I don't think.  Return the new item to Trilani and she'll give you the item to return to Bronzeleaf. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jedius98>Jedius98</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/9/01 7:34:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Finally Finished</span><hr size=1> Finally finished the quest, and I love the item...free root how can you go wrong with that?<br>
<br>
A few observations about the quest:<br>
<br>
1) To kill the courier in time before he reaches the de camp before the necro was almost dead I just reapplied my dot and then ran east.  By the time he died I had a great leg up on the courier.<br>
<br>
2) I am still not sure about the Brewing skill necessary for this quest.  I got mine up to 60 just to be safe, and got a trivial message.  This may help someone if they are wondering how high the skill should be.<br>
<br>
Thanx again! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubottlerockit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bottlerockit</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.sfachapter23.com/axelion/images/Axelion_avatar.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/17/01 2:09:31 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.sfachapter23.com/axelion/images/Axelion_avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> any tips?</span><hr size=1> I'm still on the first part of this quest - <br>
got to 24 for wolf-form (avoiding brownies) <br>
been checking tracking in LFay every time it's night-time looking for ghasts. Killed quite a few but only got 2 hearts so far.<br>
Sometimes I don't see any Ghasts on track all night long.<br>
<br>
Been killed by Equestrielle the Corrupted black horse a few times now (lost 24 once).<br>
<br>
I've read conflicting posts on different message boards about getting the ghasts to spawn.<br>
Some say kill wandering undead - some say it doesn't matter.<br>
Some suggest /locs - others say it's random.<br>
<br>
Any solid advice - other than be patient?<br>
<br>
 <p>Axelion (Arcane Evol)<BR>
Wood-Elf Druid<BR>
Mith-Marr Server<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uknightward.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KnightWard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/17/01 2:19:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: any tips?</span><hr size=1> Tho your a bit low to solo Thistle, I picked off the ghasts while searching for Ivy Cords for my friends and assisting a friend ranger slay Brownie Outcasts.<br>
<br>
Basically I ran around with track up<br>
<br>
-Fenier <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarkneill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MarkNeill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/23/01 11:14:42 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: any tips?</span><hr size=1> Have done the first 2.  Well, almost.<br>
<br>
Definitely wait until 24 to do this quest, Wolf Form will keep the brownies from aggroing.  While not whacking stuff, be Camo'd, this will prevent Equestrielle from aggroing.  Watched Equestrielle run through the Haunted Shrine 4 times last night before my camo dropped just before her 5th run.  Zoned just in time :)<br>
<br>
<br>
For the first one, I got a tip from Allakhazam.  Go to around (1000, 1000).  There should be a fairly big (for the zone) hill there.  From there, kill all wandering skeles you see.  They should be near the top of your track.  The wandering skeles seem to be the PH's for the Ghasts.  Took me about 15 ghast kills to get 4 hearts.<br>
<br>
For the second one, you can do nothing but wait.  And wait.  And wait some more.  I camped him for the better part of 4 EQ nights (prolly 12 RL hours) before I finally got him to pop.  The suggested bind location on Allakhazam is bad, if I do it again, I'd bind at the DE camp side of the route, and go back to meet the courier, rather than trying to catch him from the Steamfont zone side.<br>
<br>
Last night, popped the Necro, gated, chased the courier most of the way to the camp, before I caught him.  Beat him down, started looting, got whacked by Equestrielle before I knew she was there.  No /loc on the corpse  (*Noooooooooo*).  Got back to my corpse and looted the courier before it rotted, but in the excitement, FORGOT TO LOOT THE NECRO!  Necro rotted.  Now I have to pop him again.  Ugh. <p><FONT SIZE=+1 COLOR="#88FF88"> <I>Ailuvan Allovah</I></FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+0  COLOR="#448844"> <B>Kelethinian Wandering Druid</B> </FONT>
<BR>
